  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  a diagnosis of RA according to the ACR 1989 Criteria at least 6 months prior to
             enrollment in the study, but not longer than 12 years

          -  age 19 to 65 years old

          -  stable regimen of medication for 2 months with less than 10 mg/day of oral
             corticosteroids

          -  currently exercise &lt; 2x/week for less than 30 minutes at less than 60% of his/her age
             predicted maximum heart rate

          -  Subjects must pass the Physical Activity Readiness Scale Questionnaire (PAR-Q)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  other serious health problems

          -  intra-articular injection within 6 weeks

          -  total joint replacement of the large joints

          -  use of beta-blockers

          -  inability to complete the submaximal exercise test
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
